p: Pigs fed meat meal, poultry meal, or Tenebrio molitor diet had higher (p<0.05) SID of total energy compared to pigs fed fish meal diet ( Table 6). The SID of Arg was higher (p<0.05) in pigs fed Tenebrio molitor diet compared to that in pigs fed fish meal or meat meal diets. Furthermore, pigs fed poultry meal, meat meal, or Tenebrio molitor diet showed increased (p<0.05) SID of Cys compared to pigs fed fish meal diet. Pigs fed with Tenebrio molitor diet tended to show increased SID of DM, total energy, CP, total AAs, the rest of essential AAs (Lys, Met, Thr, Val, Ile, Leu, Phe, and His), and the rest of non-essential AAs (Asp, Ser, Glu, Gly, Ala, Tyr, and Pro) than pigs fed meat meal, poultry meal, or fish meal diet.
